        """Reverse `_serialize_for_disk`, transparently handling legacy entries.

        `diskcache` transparently pickles/unpickles non-bytes values on our behalf, so entries
        written before compression support existed (plain Python objects) come back already
        deserialized here and are returned as-is. Entries written by `_serialize_for_disk` come
